## ததஅக

[ āratti ]  
  
பெ. ārati  
1. one ofsixteen acts of worship  
consisting in the wavingof a light or lighted camphor before an idol; தீபாராதனை  
2. the waving of light  
or watermixed with saffron  
or saffroncoloured foodballs  
before important personages such as anewly wedded couple  
a ruler  
or a spiritualhead  
in processions or on other auspiciousoccasions; ஆலத்தி